WEBVTT

00:00.523 --> 00:02.073
We were able
to identify

00:02.078 --> 00:03.746
23 chromosomes
your grandson inherited

00:03.797 --> 00:05.080
from his mother.

00:05.132 --> 00:07.082
Hopefully, that's enough
to activate the machine.

00:07.134 --> 00:08.818
Previously, on <i>Fringe...</i>

00:08.886 --> 00:11.787
The machine came on by itself,
without Peter.

00:11.855 --> 00:14.223
The vortex appeared
above this field.

00:14.274 --> 00:16.976
It's the end of the world.
This is just the beginning.

00:17.060 --> 00:18.427
That machine was made for me.

00:18.495 --> 00:20.313
We all thought that I could
turn the machine on.

00:20.397 --> 00:21.898
Maybe I can turn it off.

00:21.965 --> 00:24.951
I think this is what
I'm supposed to do.

00:25.035 --> 00:26.319
I was never good
at letting you go.

00:26.386 --> 00:29.071
This time,
you have to.

00:29.122 --> 00:35.628
♪ ♪

00:37.381 --> 00:39.498
Peter!

00:41.000 --> 00:47.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:00.637 --> 01:03.623
Peter, I'm here, son.

01:14.397 --> 01:16.466
You're up.

01:16.537 --> 01:17.938
Of course.

01:17.998 --> 01:19.665
I was just resting my eyes.

01:19.716 --> 01:22.551
How is he?

01:22.636 --> 01:24.404
His pulse is strong.

01:24.405 --> 01:25.923
I just spoke with Dr. Levin.

01:25.963 --> 01:27.163
She's planning on keeping
him sedated

01:27.214 --> 01:28.631
for at least another
12 hours.

01:28.698 --> 01:30.583
She thinks the fact
that his vitals are stable

01:30.667 --> 01:33.236
is a very positive sign.

01:33.303 --> 01:34.670
She's hopeful that
he's gonna come out of this

01:34.721 --> 01:35.822
without any permanent damage.

01:35.889 --> 01:37.540
<i>She can't possibly know that.</i>

01:37.591 --> 01:39.091
Peter interacted
with a machine

01:39.176 --> 01:40.927
of immense power.

01:40.994 --> 01:44.881
Surge like that could have
disrupted his neural patterns,

01:44.948 --> 01:47.233
created memory deficits,
aphasia.

01:47.317 --> 01:51.103
Walter, let's wait and see,
okay?

01:56.860 --> 02:00.079
How about we go for a walk?

02:00.147 --> 02:01.864
You know,
you haven't eaten in hours.

02:01.915 --> 02:06.169
The cafeteria
is just downstairs.

02:09.789 --> 02:12.592
I think I saw tapioca pudding
on the menu.

02:21.218 --> 02:23.769
Well, I can't deny
I'm hungry.

02:54.001 --> 03:02.058
♪ ♪

03:24.661 --> 03:27.062
Hey, dad,
something weird is happening.

03:27.113 --> 03:29.448
What's up, Nate?
Are you feeling sick?

03:29.533 --> 03:30.616
No, I--

03:39.509 --> 03:42.077
What the hell was that?

03:42.128 --> 03:43.345
<i>Ah!</i>

03:56.259 --> 03:57.426
Are you okay, Nate?

03:57.477 --> 03:58.611
I think so.

03:58.695 --> 03:59.645
It's okay, buddy.
It's over.

03:59.729 --> 04:00.813
You wait here.

04:00.897 --> 04:02.481
I'm gonna take a look.

04:02.566 --> 04:04.033
Gary, no.
You'll be safe in the car.

04:04.100 --> 04:06.285
Just stay down,
don't touch anything.

04:28.124 --> 04:31.594
<i>No! Just stay in the car!</i>
<i>Just stay in the car.</i>

04:31.645 --> 04:33.479
Oh, my God.

04:42.022 --> 04:46.022
<font color=#ffff00>♪ Fringe 3x21 ♪</font>
<font color=#00ffff>The Last Sam Weiss</font>
